[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://gitbox.apache.org/repos/asf?p=solr.git;h=065dcfd48d8&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://gitbox.apache.org/repos/asf?p=solr.git;h=065dcfd48d8&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-17789&quot; title=&quot;Internode Authorization not working for external roles&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-17789&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-17789&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: Fix Internode Authorization not working for external roles (#3397)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When Solr forwards/proxies requests to another node that can service the request, it needs to pass authorization headers.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Allow tests to choose the number of nodes their test cluster has&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Test if solr cluster properly forwards authentication principal&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Add user principal on http context when forwarding query&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="18011074" author="jira-bot" created="Thu, 31 Jul 2025 03:09:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit eaceca8911ef06c89a293f2437a6a560f34b1a43 in solr&apos;s branch refs/heads/main from bct-timo-crabbe&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://gitbox.apache.org/repos/asf?p=solr.git;h=eaceca8911e&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://gitbox.apache.org/repos/asf?p=solr.git;h=eaceca8911e&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-17789&quot; title=&quot;Internode Authorization not working for external roles&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-17789&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-17789&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: Fix Internode Authorization not working for external roles (#3397)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When Solr forwards/proxies requests to another node that can service the request, it needs to pass authorization headers.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Allow tests to choose the number of nodes their test cluster has&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Test if solr cluster properly forwards authentication principal&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Add user principal on http context when forwarding query&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
